As a Data Scientist at OneMagnify, I manage end-to-end data science projects for Fortune 500 clients, delivering solutions that drive measurable business value. I’ve designed and implemented robust ETL pipelines, dynamic dashboards in Tableau, and predictive models to optimize client operations. My expertise in R, Python, SQL, and Tableau allows me to provide end-to-end support, from data engineering to business intelligence and advanced analytics, ensuring impactful and actionable insights for stakeholders.
My diverse skill set is further complemented by certifications in Lean Six Sigma and Continuous Improvement, as well as hands-on teaching experience, making me adept at leading technical and cross-functional teams to deliver data-driven results.





R: {tidyverse}, {duckplyr}, {data.table}
Python: Polars, Ibis
SQL: PostreSQL, MS SQL Server, DuckDB
Excel: Power Query, Pivot Tables, Data Validation, XLOOKUP/INDEX-MATCH





Static Visualizations: {ggplot2}, {gt}
Interactive Visualizations: {plotly}, {reactable}
Dynamic Documents & Presentations: Quarto





Enterprise Tools: Tableau Desktop & Prep, Power BI
Open-Source Frameworks: Shiny (R)





Web Technologies: HTML, SASS/SCSS/CSS
HTTP Libraries: {httr2}
Web Scraping Tools: {rvest}, Selenium/{RSelenium}





Model Development: {tidymodels}
Model Deployment: {vetiver}, {plumber}





Containers: Docker
Cloud Infrastructure: AWS (EC2, S3, IAM)
CI/CD: GitHub Actions
Logging: {log4r}

